      <div class="mt-16 flex w-[842px] max-w-full flex-col pb-12 max-md:mt-10">
        <div
          class="text-2xl font-semibold leading-none tracking-tighter text-white"
          tabindex="0"
        >
          Finding the problem:
        </div>
        <div
          class="mt-6 text-sm leading-5 tracking-tighter text-stone-300 max-md:max-w-full"
          tabindex="0"
        >
          The challenge for organizing meetups effectively stemmed from the lack
          of a centralized, professional, and user-friendly registration system.
          Using tools like Google Forms was functional but lacked the
          professional polish expected from India's #1 CTF and cybersecurity
          research team. Additionally, relying on external tools meant less
          control over the user data and experience, which could affect the
          trust and perception of attendees.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-10 max-md:max-w-full">
        <div class="flex gap-1">
          <div class="w-1 bg-accent"></div>
          <div class="flex min-h-[72px] flex-1 flex-col pl-7 max-md:max-w-full">
            <div
              class="text-sm font-semibold leading-none tracking-tighter text-white"
              tabindex="0"
            >
              Centralized Management
            </div>
            <div
              class="mt-3 text-sm leading-5 tracking-tighter text-stone-300 max-md:max-w-full"
              tabindex="0"
            >
              Handling registrations, attendee lists, and updates through
              multiple tools can cause friction and inefficiencies. A dedicated
              platform can streamline these processes into a unified system.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-1">
          <div class="w-1 bg-accent"></div>
          <div class="flex min-h-[72px] flex-1 flex-col pl-7 max-md:max-w-full">
            <div
